Content: There's a lot of issues with the whole jl asset system but I will say Dex payout needs to return more than 5 percent of value per year for it to be better than kmd.

Content: Dexes in general have an uphill battle as the incentive to wash trade is much lower, which is where the majority of volume comes from on central exchanges

Content: Not to mention it would be much slower and much more difficult

Author: dan.#2473
Content: I personally see great utility in dexes but do not think they will have as much revenue as people hope

Author: CoinKing88#1540
Content: It all comes down to smartly go against the market at some point, like buying BTC @ 3.5K last year and selling near the top at 12-14K. Most people want to buy when its rising and high, and are scared to buy when its low, but that's where the money is (not only in crypto). Just use DCA and ladder in where you think the bottom is (you, and not the youtubers with their own interests).

Author: CoinKing88#1540
Content: You could or course be wrong and take a loss before making a profit but sticking to a plan makes that loss bearable.
